### 1. Get all tasks (empty list at first)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

### 2. Create a new task
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn Go basics",
  "done": false
}

### 3. Create another task
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Build a REST API",
  "done": false
}

### 4. Get all tasks (should show 2 tasks now)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

### 5. Get a single task by ID (ID=1)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/1

### 6. Update a task (mark ID=1 as done)
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn Go basics",
  "done": true
}

### 7. Update a task title (ID=2)
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Build a REST API with Go",
  "done": false
}

